                    <p class="stock-description"> <strong>The Defense Prime.</strong> Largest defense contractor
                        globally. F-35 fighter jet program ($1.7T lifetime value‚Äîlargest military program in history).
                        Also: hypersonic missiles, missile defense (THAAD, PAC-3), space systems. Irreplaceable
                        contractor for US military. </p>
                    <p class="stock-description"> <strong>Why it's a buy:</strong> F-35 production ramping 156 ‚Üí 180
                        units annually through 2028 ($80M each = $14B+ revenue). Hypersonic weapons R&D ($10B+ contract
                        pipeline). $160B backlog = 2.5 years of revenue visibility. Stable 8-10% annual revenue growth,
                        2.4% dividend, recession-proof (government pays). </p>
                    <p class="stock-description"> <strong>Risks:</strong> Slow growth vs tech stocks (8% vs 30%+). Cost
                        overruns on programs. Political risk (defense budget cuts, though unlikely given geopolitics).
                    </p> <span class="conviction-level conviction-very-high">VERY HIGH CONVICTION ‚Äî 8-12%
                        PORTFOLIO</span>
