                        Technologies merger) dominates air/missile defense. Patriot missiles, AMRAAM air-to-air
                        missiles, Stinger anti-aircraft, SM-6 naval missiles. Also jet engines (Pratt & Whitney),
                        aerospace systems (Collins Aerospace). </p>
                    <p class="stock-description"> <strong>Why it's a buy:</strong> Ukraine war drove Patriot missile
                        demand through the roof‚ÄîUS replenishing stockpiles + supplying allies. NATO ordering $30B+ in
                        air defense systems. Missile production ramping 50%+ (capacity-constrained, now investing $2B in
                        factories). Backlog at $195B (3+ years revenue). Hypersonic development contracts ($8B+). </p>
                    <p class="stock-description"> <strong>Risks:</strong> Complexity (3 business units‚Äîhard to analyze).
                        Pratt & Whitney engine recalls ($5B cost). Mature stock (9% growth). </p> <span
                        class="conviction-level conviction-high">HIGH CONVICTION ‚Äî 6-10% PORTFOLIO</span>
                </div> <!-- Stock #4: General Dynamics -->
                <div class="stock-card">
